---
title: A Caesar Salad to Rule Them All with Chicken, Romaine, and Ciabatta Croutons
description: The Caesar in Caesar salad takes its name from the restaurateur who is credited with its invention, Caesar Cardini, not Julius. Nevertheless, the combo of crisp lettuce, creamy dressing, toasty croutons, and sharp Parmesan cheese rules just as hard as any Roman emperor. Our version introduces a squeeze of lemon and rosemary-seasoned chicken breasts to give it extra citrus and herb-driven power.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/a-caesar-salad-to-rule-them-all-140ab59d.jpg
